<item>
            <title>[LU-955] Lustre-modules 2.1 client rpm wrongly requires lustre-backend-fs </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-955</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I built lustre 2.1.0 based on git repo at&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jlan/lustre-nas/tree/nas-2.1.0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jlan/lustre-nas/tree/nas-2.1.0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The client lustre-modules rpm failed on rpm install:&lt;br/&gt;
error: Failed dependencies:&lt;br/&gt;
	lustre-backend-fs is needed by lustre-modules-2.1.0-1nasC_ofed153_2.6.32.23_0.3.1.20110428_nasa.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;lustre-backend-fs&quot; should not be required by a client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found a discussion thread on wc-discuss, but I do not find an LU for this problem.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://groups.google.com/a/whamcloud.com/group/wc-discuss/browse_thread/thread/d411c93a8ab28ce1#&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://groups.google.com/a/whamcloud.com/group/wc-discuss/browse_thread/thread/d411c93a8ab28ce1#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
